g.text: Uses same pinout as Adafruit STM32F4 Feather for compatibility
If trace length >10mm, ferrite beads are
Uses SPI for communication (Adafruit has library support)
VDDIO should be powered up before VDD
Note the magenetometer is a seperate SPI output and is not connected
Interrupt may need to be connected depending on later decisions
Can be removed if required, as MCU has internal oscillator.
An external oscillator will be more precise.
Capacitor values need to be determined based on crystal chosen
Uses UART for communication (NeoGPS library supports UART)
TXReady can be used as interrupt if required
Timepulse can be used for accurate timing
Fused input with reverse polarity protection, fereite bead for HF interference
Connections align with Adafruit STM32F405 Feather as much as possible for compatibility
